  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bb1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Kota flew from the Maldives!",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Maldivian media reported that President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has left Maldives for Singapore.",
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, who escaped from Katunayake Airport to Mala Island in the early morning of the 13th in an Air Force-owned Anranov aircraft, stayed there.",
        "In this case, today (14th) morning news has come out that President Gotabaya Rajapaksa did not leave Maldives for Singapore on SV788 belonging to Saudi Arabia.",
        "Meanwhile, Sri Lankan President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, who is currently traveling to Singapore, will go to Jeddah, Saudi Arabia from there, according to high-level information from the Maldives government."
      ],
